      "lecture_id": "graph_degree_challenge_001",
      "text": "The degree of a vertex is the number of edges incident to that vertex in an undirected graph. A vertex is an element of the graph's vertex set.\n"
    },
    {
      "lecture_id": "polynomial_degree_challenge_001",
      "text": "The degree of a nonzero polynomial is the largest exponent whose coefficient is nonzero. A polynomial is a finite linear combination of nonnegative integer powers of its variable.\n"
    }
  ]
